## Direct Answer to Main Question

To use SVN Revision to label build in CCNET, you can utilize the `svnRevisionLabeller` available on Google Code. This labeller allows you to incorporate the latest Subversion revision number into your build process.

## Explanation and Support from Search Results

According to the search results, there are several ways to achieve this goal. One approach is to use the `svnRevisionLabeller`, which can be found on Google Code. This tool enables you to retrieve the latest SVN revision number and incorporate it into your build process.

### Retrieving Latest SVN Revision Number

To retrieve the latest SVN revision number using the `svnRevisionLabeller`, follow these steps:

1. Download the `svnRevisionLabeller` from Google Code.
2. Modify the code slightly, as mentioned in the search results, to change the default version numbering format (major.minor.revision.build) to your desired format (major.minor.build.revision).

### Example of Modified Code

```csharp
using System;
using System.IO;

public class SvnRevisionLabeller : ILabeler
{
    public string GetLabel()
    {
        // Retrieve the latest SVN revision number
        string svnRevision = GetSvnRevision();

        // Modify the version numbering format to your desired format (major.minor.build.revision)
        string label = "1.2." + svnRevision + ".0";

        return label;
    }

    private string GetSvnRevision()
    {
        // Use SVN command-line tool to retrieve the latest revision number
        string svnCommand = "svn info --show-item revision";
        string svnRevision = ExecuteSvnCommand(svnCommand);

        return svnRevision;
    }

    private string ExecuteSvnCommand(string command)
    {
        // Execute the SVN command and capture its output
        Process process = new Process();
        process.StartInfo.FileName = "svn.exe";
        process.StartInfo.Arguments = command;
        process.StartInfo.UseShellExecute = false;
        process.StartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput = true;

        string output = process.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd();
        process.WaitForExit();

        return output.Trim();
    }
}
```

### Integrating with CCNET

To integrate the `svnRevisionLabeller` with your CCNET build process, follow these steps:

1. Add the `svnRevisionLabeller` to your CCNET project.
2. Configure the labeller in your CCNET configuration file (e.g., `ccnet.config`) to use the modified version numbering format.

### Example of CCNET Configuration

```xml
<project name="MyProject">
    <labellers>
        <labeler type="svnRevisionLabeller" />
    </labellers>

    <tasks>
        <exec command="msbuild.exe" />
    </tasks>
</project>
```

By following these steps and using the `svnRevisionLabeller`, you can successfully use SVN Revision to label your build in CCNET.

