## Using SFTP in ASP Classic

To use SFTP in ASP classic, you have several options:

### 1. Purchasing a Control

You can purchase an SFTP control that is specifically designed for ASP classic. This will provide you with a straightforward way to interact with SFTP servers.

### 2. Open Source Libraries

According to the search results, there are open-source libraries available for .NET that can be used in ASP classic projects. For example, SSH.NET is mentioned as an option for communicating with SFTP servers.

### 3. Implementing SFTP from Scratch

If you prefer not to use a control or library, you can implement SFTP functionality from scratch using the Secure Shell (SSH) protocol. This will require a good understanding of the underlying protocol and its implementation in ASP classic.

## Example Code Using SSH.NET

Here is an example of how you might use SSH.NET to connect to an SFTP server:
```csharp
using Renci.SshNet;

// Create a new SftpClient object
SftpClient sftp = new SftpClient("your_server", "username", "password");

// Connect to the SFTP server
sftp.Connect();

// Upload a file
sftp.UploadFile("local_file.txt", "/remote/path/file.txt");

// Download a file
sftp.DownloadFile("/remote/path/file.txt", "local_file.txt");

// Disconnect from the SFTP server
sftp.Disconnect();
```
This code snippet demonstrates how to connect to an SFTP server, upload and download files, and disconnect.

## Conclusion

Using SFTP in ASP classic can be achieved through various means, including purchasing a control, using open-source libraries, or implementing SFTP functionality from scratch. The example code provided above shows how to use SSH.NET to interact with an SFTP server.

