### Implementing Genetic Programming in C#

To implement genetic programming in C#, you can start by creating a basic framework that includes the following components:

1. **Genetic Algorithm**: This is the core component of genetic programming, responsible for evolving programs through selection, mutation, and crossover.
2. **Expression Trees**: These are used to represent the programs being evolved. They can be created using C#'s expression trees feature.
3. **Fitness Function**: This function evaluates the fitness of each program in the population.

Here's a basic example of how you might implement these components:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;

public class GeneticProgramming
{
    public List<Program> Evolve(int iterations)
    {
        // Initialize population with random programs
        var population = new List<Program>();

        for (int i = 0; i < iterations; i++)
        {
            // Select fittest programs
            var selected = SelectFittest(population);

            // Crossover and mutate selected programs
            var offspring = CrossoverAndMutate(selected);

            // Add offspring to population
            population.AddRange(offspring);
        }

        return population;
    }

    private List<Program> SelectFittest(List<Program> population)
    {
        // Evaluate fitness of each program in population
        foreach (var program in population)
        {
            program.Fitness = EvaluateFitness(program);
        }

        // Sort population by fitness and select top programs
        population.Sort((a, b) => a.Fitness.CompareTo(b.Fitness));
        var selected = new List<Program>(population.GetRange(0, population.Count / 2));

        return selected;
    }

    private Program CrossoverAndMutate(List<Program> selected)
    {
        // Perform crossover and mutation on selected programs
        foreach (var program in selected)
        {
            program.Crossover();
            program.Mutate();
        }

        return selected[0];
    }
}
